<body lang=EN-US style='tab-interval:.5in'>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal>Burning Woods Quad Kiting Guide </p>

<p class=MsoNormal>By Castaa of Fennin Ro</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Burning Woods is an excellent Quad Kiting zone for Wizards
level 51 through 58.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Most of the
creatures here are pure melee types.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>There are an ample amount of creatures to kill no matter the number of
people in the zone.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I suggest binding
on the crater rim opposite of the ramp leading up to the “Giant Fort” or the
zone line to Skyfire Mountains.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Both of
these areas are almost always safe from roaming creatures.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>The “quad-able” creatures in Burning Woods can be broken
into the following hit point categories:</p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h1>Low hit points (1600-1950)</h1>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak knight</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>a ash
     hornet</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     forest giant arbor</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l1 level1 lfo1;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     tatterback ape</li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<h1>Medium hit points (2400-2900)</h1>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     cinder hornet</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'>greater
     barbed skeleton</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak champion</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l5 level1 lfo2;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     tottering gorilla</li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><u>High hit points (3200-4200)<o:p></o:p></u></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'>an
     ember hornet</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'>greater
     plague skeleton</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     forest giant verdant</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     moldering gorilla</li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><u>Very high hit points (5200-6000)<o:p></o:p></u></p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     tatterback gorilla</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'>an
     forest giant ancient</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     scoriae hornet</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'>greater
     war boned skeleton</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l2 level1 lfo4;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak avenger</li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Creatures to be avoided in all cases:</p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in'>Gullerback
     (will assist any gorillas if kited nearby and is 100% magic spell
     resistant and can summon)</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in'>Wurms
     (of any type, huge melee range makes them almost impossible to quad)</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak zealot (SoW-ed Shaman caster)</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak extremist (SoW-ed Shaman caster)</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l4 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:list .5in'>a
     sarnak enthusiast (SoW-ed Shaman caster)</li>
</ul>

<p class=MsoNormal style='margin-left:.25in'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

<p class=MsoNormal>Notes:</p>

<ul style='margin-top:0in' type=disc>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Virtually
     all creatures in Burning Woods are hostile but they have a relatively
     small aggro radius.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>You can
     actually touch the tail of the wurms there without gaining aggro.<span
     style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Although I wouldn’t recommend it.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>All
     Burning Woods hornets are moderately fire resistant, use non-fire based
     spells against them if at all possible.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Giants
     will assist other giants.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Consider
     all sarnaks in Burning Woods as SoW-ed unless you see them move at
     “walking speed”.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If they appear to
     be “jogging”, they are SoW-ed.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>The
     area around the “Giant Fort” (location: 1000, 1000) is an excellent area
     to bring your quads to snare and nuke.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
     </span>So is the large flat area to the right of the of “Giant Fort’s”
     ramp.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Giants
     in Burning Woods can be stunned.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>All
     creatures will stop following you if they fall ~1000 world units
     behind.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>But they still will have
     aggro on you if you return back into their immediate area.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>All
     creatures will lose aggro on a player in ~6 minutes since the last time
     they were aggro-ed by a spell or melee attack.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>In
     most cases, it is easy to avoid creatures from attacking you.<span
     style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The only caution is need when running
     past fallen trees littered around the zones “craters”.<span
     style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Creatures can be hidden behind these
     logs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Try to run around them if at
     all possible.</li>
 <li class=MsoNormal style='mso-list:l3 level1 lfo6;tab-stops:list .5in'>Good
     luck!</li>
</ul>

</div>

</body>

